The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, Aug. 4 (PTI): A man who pleaded guilty to selling obscene pictures on mobile phones has been sentenced to stand in the courtroom till its rising. A fine of Rs 2,000 has been imposed on Deepak.

 He was caught in July last year after he took money from a decoy customer to upload such messages.

 Chandernagore: A local court has rejected the bail plea of Debu Malik, the CPM supporter held in connection with anti-land acquisition activist Tapasi Maliks murder. He has been remanded in a fortnights jail custody. 

 Calcutta: A fire, possibly caused by short circuit, broke out at a Tiljala rubber factory on Saturday. The workers managed to rush out in time, the fire brigade said.




